http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Five-tiger-deaths-in-PTR/article13978300.ece

The Wildlife Protection Society of India (WPSI) statistics show that out of six tiger deaths in the State last year, three were due to infighting and three killed by other animals. Five of these deaths were in the Periyar Tiger Reserve and one in the Wayanad Wildlife Sanctuary.While data provided by the National Tiger Conservation Authority show that there were 69 wild tiger deaths across the country last year, data provided by the WPSI show that there were 79 wild tiger deaths in the country last year.